  <Description>Medium rare roasted beef with a nice relish.</Description>
  <Prerequisites>
    <Prerequisite>8 hours ahead: Stir 1 1/2 teaspoons granulated garlic, 1 1/2 teaspoons kosher salt, and 1 1/2 teaspoons coarsely ground black pepper together in a small bowl. Pat 1 (about 2 1/2-pound) beef tri-tip roast dry with paper towels. If there is any silver skin on the surface, trim it off (here's how). Rub all over with the garlic mixture.Refrigerate uncovered. </Prerequisite>
    <Prerequisite>Preheat oven to 450°F.</Prerequisite>
  </Prerequisites>
